  <static seed="31" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/PolynomialMultiplication/PolynomialMultiplication160.pg">
    <statement><p>Multiply the polynomials.</p>
<p><m>\left({y-5}\right)\left({y+5}\right)=</m><fillin characters="32" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>y^{2}-25</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>We use the FOIL technique- <alert>F</alert>irst <alert>O</alert>utside <alert>I</alert>nside <alert>L</alert>ast</p>
<p><m>\begin{aligned}
              \left({y-5}\right)({y+5})\amp ={y^{2}+5y-5y-25}\\
                                \amp ={y^{2}-25}
      \end{aligned}</m></p>
<p>Alternatively, we might observe that this is the product of <em>the sum and difference of two terms</em>, in which case we may use the formula</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{(a-b)(a+b)=a^2-b^2}</m></p>
<p>and write</p>
<p><m>\begin{aligned}
              \left({y-5}\right)({y+5})\amp =y^2-5^2\\
                                \amp ={y^{2}-25}
      \end{aligned}</m></p>
<p>which is the same result we obtained using the FOIL method.</p>
</solution>
